## Branch Strategy

### Branches

| branch        | use                                      |
| -------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `main`        | Production main branch, always deployable |
| `feature/<name>` | New features                          |
| `fix/<name>`  | Bug fixes                                |
| `docs/<name>` | Docs work (as needed)                    |

### Rules

- Keep branch names short and clear (e.g. `feature/about-page`, `fix/nav-overlap`)
- After merging into `main`, delete the branch
- Use separate branches for different features

### Branch Creation (when committing)

| situation                                  | decision      | branch           |
| ------------------------------------------ | ------------- | ---------------- |
| `feat` (new page, feature)                  | create branch | `feature/<name>` |
| `fix` (bug fix)                             | create branch | `fix/<name>`     |
| `docs`, `chore`, `style`                    | commit to main | -              |
| Many files (5+) or multiple features        | create branch | appropriate type |
| Small change (few files, minor)             | commit to main | -              |

- When unsure, prefer creating a branch

